===[[Etymology]]===
F. <ets>accompagnement</ets>.
===[[Noun]]===, ''giving support or adding to the background in music, adding for ornamentation''. 
(''Webster'') That which accompanies; something that attends as a circumstance, or which is added to give greater completeness to the principal thing, or by way of ornament, or for the sake of symmetry</def>. Specifically: <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A part performed by instruments, accompanying another part or parts performed by voices; the subordinate part, or parts, accompanying the voice or a principal instrument; also, the harmony of a figured bass.
<i>P. Cyc.</i></i>
